## Before drafting, read these conventions

The `jira-conventions` skill is the canonical index for the rules below — read it first if it isn't already loaded into context. Then read the four references in order, applying as you go:

1. `~/.claude/references/jira-comment-style.md` — voice, structure, analysis vs. status-update distinction
2. `~/.claude/references/jira-draft-frontmatter.md` — required YAML frontmatter, post-state tracking, why ADF over markdown
3. `~/.claude/references/jira-mention-convention.md` — `@{Display Name}` drafting syntax, resolution rules
4. `~/.claude/references/jira-adf-reference.md` — ADF node patterns for mentions, links, nested bullets

If a reference is missing, report that to the user before proceeding.

